quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  106,1,"for the lasting security of Quraysh{1}—",footnotes:1:The tribe of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him).
  106,2,"their lasting security during winter and summer journeys—"
  106,3,"so let them worship the Lord of this House,"
  106,4,"who has fed them to ward off hunger and has secured them to ward off fear."
  107,1,"Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>seen the one who denies the Recompense{1}?",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is deenwhich means ‘a way of life’, ‘religion’ or ‘recompense’.
  107,2,"It is the one who mistreats the orphan"
  107,3,"and does not urge<i class=""s"">(others to serve) </i>food to the destitute<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>."
  107,4,"So woe to the ones who pray—"
  107,5,"those who are heedless of their prayers,"
  107,6,"those who make show<i class=""s"">(of their deeds) </i>"
  107,7,"yet withhold<i class=""s"">(little) </i>kindnesses{1}.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is ma’oun; it denotes small acts of help like lending house utensils, the withholding of which is a sign of stinginess.
  108,1,"Indeed, We have given you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>plenty{1}.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is AlKawthar, which is also the name of a river in Paradise.
  108,2,"So pray to your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord and sacrifice."
  108,3,"Indeed, it is the one who hates you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>who has been cut off."
